Governor  Aminu Waziri Tambuwal of Sokoto State has appointed Saidu Umar as the Secretary to the State Government.
National Daily learned that the Director General, Media and Public Affairs to the Governor, Abubakar Shekara, made the announcement in a statement on Thursday.
ALSO READ: June 12: Rivers group to address insecurity in Nigeria on new Democracy Day
The Media Director highlighted that Saidu was a former Commissioner for Finance in the last Executive Council of the state.
Also, Governor Tambuwal   reappointed Muktar Umar Magori as Chief of Staff, Government House, Sokoto.
The governor encouraged the appointees to re-dedicate themselves to the service of the people, while praying Allah to guide them in their assigned tasks.








			
